            <scopecontent id="aspace_cffdd9162eaa38c957ac309da14c07f5">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>The Thomas Ewart Marston Papers consist entirely of notes taken by Marston between 1936 and 1937 from documents in the British Public Records Office, the India Office, and the British Museum relating to Aden, Abyssinia, and Arabia from 1800-1878. Marston probably used this research in writing <emph render="italic">Britain's Imperial Role in the Red Sea Area, 1800-1878</emph>, which was published in 1961. The notes are arranged as Marston arranged them, by location of the records.</p>
            </scopecontent>
